      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:34:5",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ أَقَرَّ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ بِحَدٍّ أَقَمْتُهُ عَلَيْهِ إِلَّا الرَّجْمَ فَإِنَّهُ إِذَا أَقَرَّ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ ثُمَّ جَحَدَ لَمْ يُرْجَمْ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Abu Ayoub, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who accepts upon himself with a Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>), it would be established upon him, except for the stoning. So if he were to accept upon himself, then deny, he would not be stoned’."
        ]
      }
    }
